@NODE GLOSSARY "Glossar"
@{b}@{u}4.3 Glossar@{uu}@{ub}

Aspect          Describes the ratio of width to height of a pixel.
                An aspect of 4:5 means that a pixel has a width of 4 units
                and a height of 5 units. The aspect is important with
                picture painted on computers. Scanned pictures generally
                have an aspect of 1:1.

Bézier curve    A Bézier curve is described by a start.-, a end.- and two
                points to divert the curve. The curve pass from the start.-
                to the end-point and is diverted by the other two points,
                as would these points be magnets. Thereby simple curves
                can be described with only 4 points. More complexe curves
                are described with several Bézier curves.

Bitmap storage  The bitmap of loaded pictures can be stored into RAM using
          type  3 different ways, which differs at speed and memory
                consumption :

                Planar  - Data is stored into bitplanes, which respectively
                          contains only one bit of any pixel.
                          As number of bits per pixel, 1 .. 8 is possible.

                          Advant.  : - Low memory consumption
                                     - nearly no wasted memory
                                     - more than one small memory blocks
                                       (for depth larger than 1)
 
                          Disadv.  : - generally slower than Chunky and
                                       ByteMap

                Chunky  - Data is stored successively for every pixel.
                          As number of bits per pixel, 1, 2, 4 and 8 is
                          possible (because of speed).

                          Advant.  : - generally faster than planar
                                     - at depths of 1, 2, 4 or 8
                                       more less memory consumption than
                                       Planar
 
                          Disadv.  : - generally slower than ByteMap
                                     - higher memory consumption at 
                                       depth of 3 or 5 .. 7 than Planar
                                       (see above) because of unused bits
                                     - one large memory block

                ByteMap - Every pixel will be stored, independent of the
                          depth, in one byte.

                          Advant.  : - much faster than Planar or Chunky
                                     - at a depth of 8 less/equal 
                                       memory consumption than/like Planar
                                       or Chunky.
 
                          Disadv.  : - higher memory consumption at
                                       depths of 1 .. 7 than Planar or
                                       Chunky (see above) because of unused
                                       bits
                                     - one large memory block

                You can select the storage type to use with the @{"settings" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_SETSTORTYPE }.

Clipboard       Memory used by the system to save CLIPS: The maximum number
                of available clipboards is 256 (0 .. 255). Only IFF-files
                can used with the clipboards.
                XTrace uses a @{"Clipboard-Requester" link XTrace_Usage.guide/WIN_CLIPBOARD } to make its handling
                easier.

Color-Type      XTrace uses 3 internal color types

                Palette - The picture can use up to 256 colors. The color
                          values can be changed, operators like 
                          @{b}Edge Detection@{ub} are not available.

                Gray    - The picture can use up to 256 fixes grayscales.
                          You can not change them. Operators like Remove
                          Unused Colors or Edit Palette are @{b}not@{ub}
                          available.

                B/W     - black / white - like gray but only with 2
                          grayscales

                For bitmap pictures these colortypes can be converted from
                one to another with the menue @{"Convert color" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_CONVCOLOR }.
                For vector pictures the colortype is not important.

DPI             @{b}D@{ub}ots @{b}p@{ub}er @{b}i@{ub}nch

GUI             @{b}G@{ub}raphic @{b}U@{ub}ser @{b}I@{ub}nterface

HSB             A color model like RGB. It's a subtractive mixture of a
                @{b}H@{ub}ue-, a @{b}S@{ub}aturation- and a @{b}B@{ub}rightness-value.
                This model is excellent for manual color mixture. The
                values of HSB colors, are the position of the Hue-value on
                the colorwheel and the procental values of the saturation
                and brightness.

IFF XTVF        Internal file format of XTrace (@{b}XT@{ub}race @{b}V@{ub}ector @{b}F@{ub}ormat)
                used to save all data of the bitmap and vector picture.

Keyfile         A keyfile is a file, personalized for you (and only for
                you), which will enable all blocked functions and disable
                all demo reminders of XTrace.

                You will get your keyfile, when you are @{"registered" link XTrace_Introduction.guide/REGISTER}.

                For better understandig: There is only one version of
                XTrace, which works as unregistered version, if there is
                no keyfile or it works as registered version, if it found
                your keyfile.
                
                This means, you can download/copy every new version of
                XTrace and if you're @{"registered" link XTrace_Introduction.guide/REGISTER}, it will work with all
                functions, if not it will be the demo version.

                So I don't need to send you every new release, just
                download/copy it (cheaper, faster and save ressources).

Object          Made of several (or many) vectors.

RGB             A color model like HSB. It's an additive mixture of a
                a @{b}R@{ub}ed-, a @{b}B@{ub}lue- and a @{b}G@{ub}reen-value.
                This color model is not as suitable as the HSB model to
                mix the desired color. The values range for each R, G and B
                from 0 .. 255, which gives a total range of 16.777.216
                different colors. (By the way, the human eye can distinguish
                only about 7.000.000 color tones at maximum.)

Used Colors     The maximum possible number of colors per picture is
                defined by its depth. A depth of e.g. 5 means 2^5 = 32
                possible colors. If this maximum number of available colors
                not used by the picture, and you have choosen the menue
                item @{"Remove unused colors" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_REMUNUSED} the unused colors will be move
                closer together and the unused ones will be marked as unused 
                and unused memory will be freed.

Vectors         Is made of coordinates, which are used to draw the vector
                picture. Several (or a lot of) vectors define an object.

XPK             E@{b}x@{ub}ternal @{b}P@{ub}ac@{b}k@{ub}er - A modular packer concept, used to
                compress files with different algorithms (compressor-
                libraries in the LIBS:Compressors directory).
@ENDNODE

@NODE KNOWNBUGS "Known bugs resp. problems"
@{b}@{u}4.4 Known bugs resp. problems@{uu}@{ub}

 - sometimes the slope function creates Bézier curves that are larger than
   the object to convert. This can be corrected (sometimes) if you set the
   accuracy to lower values. (See @{"Slope" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_SLOPE } chapter for values giving best
   results.)
   This is not really a bug, but a general problem at usage of bézier curves.

 - if you have started XTrace under a system configuration without a 
   _saved_ (via Prefs/Pointer) mouse pointer (means in EnvArc:SYS/ is
   no file named 'Pointer.prefs') all tool pointer appear only colored
   black and not with the orginal mouse colors.

   This is _no_ bug of XTrace but from OS 3.1 (resp. OS 3.0 also, but this
   is untested).

   Should you have this problem start the program 'Pointer' from your Prefs
   drawer and select 'Save'.

 - Problems with screenmodes with a depth <= 8 bit and the ColorDisplay
   gadgets (e.g. in the PenDisplay window) (e.g. wrong colors while editing
   the palette) can occur if you've installed MagicMenu, because MM patches
   the intuition.library function ObtainGIRPort() in a way which forbids
   the gadgets to use their rastport and clear their paint area.
@ENDNODE

@NODE HISTORY "History"
@{b}@{u}4.5 History@{uu}@{ub}

 @{u}Means of abbreviations :@{uu}

 CNG : Changed       REV : Revised
 IMP : Improved      REW : Rewritten
 REM : Removed       FIX : Fixed
 ADD : Added         WAR : Workarounded

 @{u}@{b}V 1.00 Evolution Level 18249 - Aminet Release 30-Apr-1996@{ub}@{uu}

  - first released version

 @{u}@{b}V 1.01 Evolution Level 18475 - Aminet Release 13-May-1996@{ub}@{uu}

  CHG: changed limitations for unregistered users

  FIX: fixed some bugs (reported by Michael Merkel & André Rothe)

  CHG: Settings completely changed. This was necessary, so that future
       changes automatically change the old settings without loosing them.
       There are now main- and temporary settings

  ADD: Worldmap included

  IMP: @{"Slope" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_SLOPE } improved

  @{b}Warning :@{ub}

  - you must delete the setting-file(s) of XTrace if you update from V1.00
    to V1.01 from the XTrace-Directory/Prefs directory. If you don't do
    it, problems with grayscale display can occur.

  @{u}@{b}V 1.10 Evolution Level 20492 - Aminet Release 30-Sep-1996@{ub}@{uu}

  FIX: some bugs fixed

  CHG: @{"Monitor settings" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_SETMONITOR } changed

  CHG: @{"Toolbox" link XTrace_Usage.guide/WIN_TOOLS } changed (PageStream® like) (idea by Manfred Böhm)

  CHG: @{"Frame tool" link XTrace_Usage.guide/WIN_TOOLS } improved (now with own color)  

  ADD: Displaying vectors in picture windows now possible

  IMP: @{"IFF XTVF" link XTrace_Miscellaneous.guide/FORMATS } format improved

  IMP: @{"EPSI" link XTrace_Miscellaneous.guide/FORMATS } preview improved

  ADD: @{"EPSB" link XTrace_Miscellaneous.guide/FORMATS } exporter added

  IMP: Online help is now asynch., that means the guide runs independent
       from XTrace

  ADD: Vector operator "Remove pen" to remove background objects for
       transparent background added

  REV: @{"Slope" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_SLOPE } completely revised and improved

  IMP: @{"Display histogram" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_DISPHISTO } improved

  ADD: @{"Stretch histogram" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_STRCHISTO } added

  ADD: @{"Equalize histogram" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_EQUAHISTO } added

  ADD: @{"Invert" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_INVERT } added

  ADD: @{"Flip" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_FLIP } for bitmap picture added

  ADD: @{"Thinning" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_THINNING } added

  REV: Bitmap- and vector process menues

  ADD: @{"Bitmap storage type" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_SETSTORTYPE } added

  ADD: Digital filters improved for working with @{"filter sequences" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_FILTERSEQ }

  ADD: English documentation (Thanks, Manou :-))

  REM: Adjust brightness, contrast and saturation
  
  ADD: @{"Global color control" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_GLOBCOLCON} as replacement for Adjust ... (see above)
       added

 @{u}@{b}V 1.20 Evolution Level 22833 - Aminet Release 17-Jul-1997@{ub}@{uu}

  FIX: some bugs fixed

  FIX: bug at using @{"Equalize histogram" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_EQUAHISTO} and 
       @{"Global color control" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_GLOBCOLCON } with fewer grayscales than
       256 fixed

  ADD: @{"Edge detection" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_EDGEDETECT} added

  IMP: Online help handling via AmigaGuide® improved

  IMP: @{"Trace" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_TRACE} speeded up 

  IMP: Behaviour of XTrace at multiple executing improved
       (reported by Andreas Kleinert)

  FIX: Bug at Scale fixed

  FIX: Problems at Trace in junction with the triangle division removed.

  WAR: Because of a bug, inside a datatype or OS 3.0, some pictures were 
       loaded via a datatype as a one-colored area. XTrace now recognizes
       this bug and tried to bypass this one. (-> Volker Schmidt)

  REM: AreaInside option at Trace removed
      
  IMP: Vector operator "Remove pen" improved to @{"Make pen transparent" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_MAKEPENTRANS}
       which can make *every* pen, indepenently from the picture, transparent.

  IMP: @{"Vector / Object Banks" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_SETBANKS} are now full dynamic.

  ADD: Capability to export pictures as 3D logos for Michiel den Outer's
       "Navigator Titler" (see @{"FAQ" link XTrace_Miscellaneous.guide/FAQ} also).

  ADD: Capablity to load, trace and export fonts as 3D fonts for Michiel
       den Outer's "Navigator Titler" (see @{"FAQ" link XTrace_Miscellaneous.guide/FAQ} also).

  CNG: Slope operator settings changed.

  ADD: @{"DXF 2D" link XTrace_Miscellaneous.guide/FORMATS} and @{"DXF 3D" link XTrace_Miscellaneous.guide/FORMATS} exporter

  ADD: @{"Eyedropper tool" link XTrace_Usage.guide/WIN_TOOLS} is now usable for vector pictures also

  IMP: Handling of @{"Eyedropper tool" link XTrace_Usage.guide/WIN_TOOLS} improved

 @{u}@{b}V 2.00 Evolution Level 25372 - Aminet Release 03-Jun-1998@{ub}@{uu}

  ADD: "Display traces" option for @{"Trace" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_TRACE} (-> André Rothe)

  ADD: @{"FIG" link XTrace_Miscellaneous.guide/FORMATS} exporter (-> Volker Schmidt)

  IMP: @{"Supress noise" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_SUPNOISE} slightly improved

  IMP: @{"Apply Digital Filter Sequence" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_FILTERSEQ} slightly improved

  ADD: Full CyberGraphX/Picasso96 support
       (if you choose a screen deeper than 8 bit for the XTrace screen, the
        pictures will be displayed colored)

  CHG: @{"Monitor settings" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_SETMONITOR }

  CHG: @{"Thinning" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_THINNING} can now handle also other @{"Color-Type" link GLOSSARY}s than only 'B/W'.
        (-> Volker Schmidt)

  IMP: @{"Permanent Windows" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_SETPERMWINS} settings

  ADD: @{"Log window" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_LOG} incl. some options

  ADD: Own routines for displaying filled polygons as replacement for the
       Area() commands. No chip memory more needed.

  ADD: Lens und Hand @{"tool" link XTrace_Usage.guide/WIN_TOOLS} now also available for vector pictures.

  REM: Worldmap

  ADD: Operator @{"Remove pen" LINK XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_REMOVEPEN}

  IMP: @{"Slope" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_SLOPE } (again ...)

  ADD: @{"Adobe Illustrator®" link XTrace_Miscellaneous.guide/FORMATS} exporter

  IMP: @{"DXF 2D" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_SETDXF2D} exporter capabilities slightly improved

  ADD: @{"HP-GL" link XTrace_Miscellaneous.guide/FORMATS} exporter

  IMP: @{"Display histograms" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_DISPHISTO} can now display seperate histograms for
       red, green and blue parts, as well as brightness and saturation parts
       and the orginal histogram.

  IMP: @{"Stretch histogram" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_STRCHISTO} and @{"Equalize histogram" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_EQUAHISTO} now available for all
       @{"Color-Types" link GLOSSARY}.

  IMP: @{"EPS exporter" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_SETEPS}

  ADD: @{"Adaptive histogram equalization" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_ADAPTHISTEQUAL}

  ADD: @{"Apply Digital Filter Sequence" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_FILTERSEQ} works internally always with 8 (for
       Grayscales and B/W pictures) or 24 (for palette pictures) bit now.

  ADD: Base-shapes and new divider/bias calculation for filters
       (@{"Edit filter" link XTrace_Usage.guide/WIN_EDITFILTER})

  CHG: Fileformat of filters, filtersequences, colorcurves and settings 
       changed to a more portable text format. Please convert your own 
       filters, filtersequences and colorcurves with the enclosed program
       @{"'FileFormatConverter'" LINK XTrace_Usage.guide/FILEFORMATCONVERTER}. The settings are not convertable, please set your
       preferences new and save them.

  ADD: A remark for every filter, filtersequence and colorcurve can now be
       stored (for example the effect of the filter).

  ADD: Operator @{"Edge enhancement" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_EDGEENHANCE}

  IMP: Operator @{"Edge detection" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_EDGEDETECT}

  IMP: @{"Picture window title" link XTrace_Usage.guide/WIN_PICTURE}

  IMP: @{"Loaded pictures list" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_LOADEDPL}

  ADD: @{"Close bitmap part" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_CLOSEBITMAPPART} and @{"Close vector part" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_CLOSEVECTORPART}

  ADD: Operator @{"Coalesce colors" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_COALESCECOLORS}

  ADD: Filtersets for digital filters (@{"Apply Digital Filter Sequence" link XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_FILTERSEQ},
       @{"Edit filter" link XTrace_Usage.guide/WIN_EDITFILTER})

  NEW: @{"Remove isolated pixels" LINK XTrace_Usage.guide/MENU_REMISOLATEDPIXELS} operator
@ENDNODE

@NODE ADVERTISEMENT "Advertisement"
@{b}@{u}4.6 Advertisement@{uu}@{ub}

 Other released programs on Aminet by me:

 - LoC V 1.2, (aminet:dev/c)

   Counts the lines in C-source code (sorted as code, comments, spaces)

 - XStat V 1.4, (aminet:util/pack)

   Does some statistics on several XPK-packed files.

 - Galaxy V 1.00, (aminet:util/blank)

   Blankermodule for Garshneblanker: draws rotating and collapsing galaxies.

 - TurningGlobe V 1.2 (aminet:util/wb)

   Displays a small, spinning globe at a public screen.
@ENDNODE
